HEADWORD: Mushroom-headed
<hw>Mush"room-head`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Having a cylindrical body with a convex head of larger diameter;
having a head like that of a mushroom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

